results.description: One pictured here, but there is a mating pair I observed here for most of the winter months. Didn't ever get the chance to see their young. Dissecting about 20 dried pellets I found they eat mostly voles, but I'm not a scientist so my analysis of the species can be wrong. The male here is very habituated to humans and is the only one I've ever encountered that doesn't fly off when you get within 20 feet of it. I see the male 9/10 times I go to the preserve near sunset in the winter.
